Lectura de la base de datos.

ejemplo <- read.csv2( "ejemplo1.csv" )

Exploratorio inicial.

library(geoR)
geo_ejemplo <- as.geodata(ejemplo)
summary(geo_ejemplo)

Semivariograma isotr√≥pico.

semivario1 <- variog(geo_ejemplo, max.dist = 650, uvec = 20)
## variog: computing omnidirectional variogram
plot(semivario1)

Semivariogramas direccionales.

semivario1_4 <- variog4(geo_ejemplo, max.dist = 650, uvec = 20)
## variog: computing variogram for direction = 0 degrees (0 radians)
##         tolerance angle = 22.5 degrees (0.393 radians)

##         tolerance angle = 22.5 degrees (0.393 radians)

plot(semivario1_4)

Semivariograma direccionales teniendo en cuenta la tendencia.

semivario2_4 <- variog4(geo_ejemplo, max.dist = 650, uvec = 20, trend = "1st")
## variog: computing variogram for direction = 0 degrees (0 radians)
##         tolerance angle = 22.5 degrees (0.393 radians)

plot(semivario2_4, lwd = 3)

Predicci√≥n del modelo.

puntos_pred <- pred_grid(c(0, 700), c(0, 600), by = 5)

KC <- krige.control(type = "OK", obj.mod = m1)
sk <- krige.conv(geo_ejemplo, krige = KC, loc = puntos_pred)
## krige.conv: model with mean given by a 1st order polynomial on the coordinates
## krige.conv: anisotropy correction performed
## krige.conv: Kriging performed using global neighbourhood
## krige.conv: model with constant mean
## krige.conv: Kriging performed using global neighbourhood
pred.lim <- range(c(sk$pred))
sd.lim <- range(sqrt(c(sk$kr)))
image(sk, col = gray(seq(0, 0.8, l = 101)), zlim = pred.lim)
contour(sk, add = T, levels = seq(250, 450, 20), col = "blue")
points(geo_ejemplo, add = TRUE, cex.max = 2)
